## 2. Scaffold pointer — clone from Maryland WP demo

**The Maryland demo is the proven scaffold.** Clone every pattern:

| Pattern | Maryland | Panhandle (change to) |
|---|---|---|
| Bridge file | `maryland_driveway_wp_bridge_blueprint.py` | `panhandle_wp_bridge_blueprint.py` |
| Blueprint var | `bridge_bp as mdr_wp_bridge_bp` | `bridge_bp as panhandle_wp_bridge_bp` |
| PREFIX | `"demos/maryland-driveway-restore"` | `"demos/panhandle-garage-door-company"` |
| UPSTREAM | `"http://127.0.0.1:8081"` | `"http://127.0.0.1:8090"` |
| Service name | `mdr-wordpress-docker` | `panhandle-wp` |
| Docker network prefix | `mdr-` | `panhandle-` |
| WP port | 8081 | 8090 |
| DB name | (varies) | `panhandle` |

**server.py insertion point:** after line 350 (after Maryland bridge block):
```python
# --- Panhandle Garage Door WP demo bridge ---
from panhandle_wp_bridge_blueprint import bridge_bp as panhandle_wp_bridge_bp
app.register_blueprint(panhandle_wp_bridge_bp)
```

**CRITICAL bridge flags (copy verbatim from Maryland bridge):**
- `_NoRedirect` opener — never follow redirects
- `Host: api.michaelwegter.com` + `X-Forwarded-Proto: https` injected
- Strip `accept-encoding` in `_HOP` set to prevent gzip/brotli corruption
- `_HOP` must include `content-encoding` and `accept-encoding`

