## 5. Surface runner service registration (critical for Docker pull + restart durability)

```python
# surface_register_panhandle_wp.py (send via scripts/surface_run.py)
# ASCII-only. Registers panhandle-wp so run-server.ps1 owns startup.
NAME = "panhandle-wp"
CMD = "docker"
ARGS = ["compose", "-f", "panhandle_wp/docker-compose.yml", "up", "-d", "--wait"]
CWD = "."   # runner workspace
PORT = 8090
```

Run `surface_register_service.py` with these values. Wait for `LISTENING` on port 8090 before proceeding. First run will pull images (minutes); subsequent starts are fast.

